 aural methods, they explore how each approach worked in practice, what the benefits and pitfalls were, and what the wider and future application of the chosen research methods might be. Covering a wide range of subjects from non-resident fathers to father engagement in child protection, this major contribution to the field also critiques and addresses the notion that fathers, especially young fathers, can be ‘hard to reach’. Essential reading for both students and policy makers in a fast-growing area of interest.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aFatherhood. 0aFathers. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Marriage & Family.2bisacsh1 aBosoni, Maria Letizia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurnett, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChawla-Duggan, Rita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaneback, Kristian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDermott, Esther, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDermott, Esther, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGatrell, Caroline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGatrell, Caroline, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIves, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLau-Clayton, Carmen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMazzucchelli, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Tina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMilner, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlantin, Lars, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSymonds, Jon, e